A  has m1() and performing m1() it goes to state B 
B has m2() and performing it goes to state C.
And in state C perform m3() and goes to state A.
(STATE MACHINE DIAGRAM) -->refer notes

If there are limited number of states and limited number of methods and on every methid ut changes its state we can use STATE DESIGN PATTERN.

Example:
Vending Machine 
Vending Machine hs lot of items and to interact with it we have a panel with screen and keypad. And has a despenSer to collect the item.
1.When no one is using it ---NO COIN STATE
2.When insert a coin---HAS COIN STATE
3.Selecting item.---DESPENSE STATE
4.SOLD OUT STATE